<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.011/431</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 389</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-08">June 8, 1940</date>.<lb/>[Received June
                                10.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing my despatch No. 378, of June
                            6, 1940, I have the honor to report that the transitory provision
                            covering the moratoria <pb facs="0784" n="772" xml:id="pg_772"/> was
                            published in yesterday’s <hi rend="italic">Official Gazette</hi>. A copy
                            is enclosed.<note n="57" xml:id="d910fn1">See <hi rend="italic">Gaceta
                                    Oficial</hi>, June 7, 1940, pp. 11, 905–11, 908.</note></p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">George S.
                            Messersmith</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>